        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15934",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To prevent the creation of a translation object without the possibility of translation you MUST give minimum one source at creation...\n\nThis is expected behaviour and decreases possible problems.\n\nYour point one and three are identical...\nBtw: The deletion of the existing translation source is unneccessary at time of the object creation because at this time there is no existing source avaiable.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-21T17:00:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-21T17:00:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15940",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changed the contructor with SVN 5809.\nAfter review it will be added with 1.0.1",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-23T04:57:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-23T04:57:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15945",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{code}\n-\t    public function __construct($adapter, $options, $locale = null)\n+\t    public function __construct($adapter, $data, $locale = null, array $options = array())\n{code}\n\nI agree this would have been the best way to design this constructor arguments, but this is a problem now because this change breaks backward-compatibility.  My understanding is that this is not okay after 1.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-23T09:00:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-23T09:00:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15946",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why do you believe it breaks backwards compatibility ???\n\nThe internal name of the variable is not breaking this.\nI could also name it like this:\n\n{code}\npublic function __construct($adapter, $options, $locale = null, array $adapteroptions = array())\n{code}\n\nAs you can see here it does not break the compatibility:\n\n{code}\n-    public function __construct($adapter, $options, $locale = null)\n+    public function __construct($adapter, $data, $locale = null, array $options = array())\n     {\n-        $this->setAdapter($adapter, $options, $locale);\n+        $this->setAdapter($adapter, $data, $locale, $options);\n     }\n{code}\n\nI just renamed the second argument because it then has the same named arguments as the internal called \"setAdapter\" method.  As you see the second argument is passed as second to setAdapter as before the change which does not break the compatibility.\n\nI would see a problem if the arguments would have changed their position. But this has not happend.\n\nIf you believe the internal name of the argument breaks the backwards compatibility I can also rename it as described above.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-23T10:09:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-23T10:09:39.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
